# RCLP API Reference

## rclp.RCLP_KEM

The main key encapsulation mechanism.

```python
from rclp import RCLP_KEM

kem = RCLP_KEM(security_bits=128)  # 128, 192, or 256

pk, sk = kem.keygen(seed=None)
ct, shared_secret = kem.encapsulate(pk, seed=None)
shared_secret = kem.decapsulate(sk, ct)

# Size queries
kem.public_key_size()   # bytes
kem.secret_key_size()   # bytes
kem.ciphertext_size()   # bytes
```

## rclp.GolayCode

The [24,12,8] extended binary Golay code.

```python
from rclp import GolayCode

g = GolayCode()
g.codewords       # np.array shape (4096, 24)
g.weights          # np.array shape (4096,)
g.octads()         # list of 759 frozensets
g.dodecads()       # list of 2576 frozensets
g.hexadecads()     # list of 759 frozensets

# Verification
g.verify_weight_distribution()  # bool
g.verify_self_duality()         # bool
g.verify_steiner_system()       # bool

# Decoding
decoded, hamming_dist = g.decode_nearest_codeword(received_word)

# Partition functions (exact rational)
F = g.partition_function(weight=8, s=2)  # returns Fraction

# Sign-change automorphism (the fundamental flip)
flipped = GolayCode.apply_sign_change(codeword, vector)
```

## rclp.LeechLattice

The Leech lattice Λ₂₄ constructed from the Golay code.

```python
from rclp import LeechLattice

L = LeechLattice()
L.build_type_a()              # 1,104 vectors
L.build_type_b()              # 97,152 vectors (slow)
L.build_type_c()              # 98,304 vectors (slow)
L.all_minimal_vectors()       # all 196,560

L.verify_kissing_number()     # bool
L.verify_norms()              # bool
L.verify_antipodal()          # bool
L.verify_sign_change_preservation()  # bool
```

## rclp.TwoSidedSurface / rclp.EnrichedFlip

The enriched two-sided surface model.

```python
from rclp import TwoSidedSurface, EnrichedFlip
from rclp.surface import SurfaceState, BITS_PER_SIDE

# Create a random two-sided surface
s = TwoSidedSurface.random()
s.flip()                    # atomic total swap
s.visible_state()           # outer SurfaceState
s.hidden_state()            # inner SurfaceState
s.is_flipped()              # bool

# Apply Golay-constrained flip to 24 surfaces
flipper = EnrichedFlip()
surfaces = [TwoSidedSurface.random() for _ in range(24)]
flipper.apply(surfaces, codeword)
flipper.is_valid_pattern(pattern)  # bool
EnrichedFlip.payload_bits(8)       # 1536
EnrichedFlip.amplification_factor()  # 129.0
```

## rclp.BabaiGolayDecoder

The optimal RCLP decoder.

```python
from rclp import BabaiGolayDecoder

dec = BabaiGolayDecoder()
codeword, n_corrections = dec.decode(base_point, unflipped_observation)
p = BabaiGolayDecoder.minimum_coordinate_sample(q=31, min_coord=4)
```

## rclp.Quaternion / rclp.Octonion / rclp.Sedenion

Hypercomplex arithmetic over Z or Z_q.

```python
from rclp import Quaternion, Octonion, Sedenion

a = Quaternion([1, 2, 3, 4], modulus=127)
b = Quaternion([5, 6, 7, 8], modulus=127)
c = a * b  # non-commutative: a*b != b*a

s_a, s_b = Sedenion.known_zero_divisor()
assert (s_a * s_b).is_zero()  # verified zero-divisor pair
```
